ADDITIONAL ENGINEERING REQUIREMENTS

The following rules extend the project instructions and must always be respected.

------------------------------------------------
CODE STANDARDS

Use consistent naming conventions across the project.

JavaScript:
camelCase for variables and functions

Database fields:
snake_case

Files and folders:
kebab-case

Avoid large files and prefer modular components.

------------------------------------------------
TESTING STRATEGY

Critical system functionality must include tests.

Prioritize tests for:

reservation creation
table assignment logic
API endpoints
automation triggers

Tests should be stored in a /tests directory.

------------------------------------------------
SECURITY PRACTICES

Never store secrets in the repository.

Sensitive credentials must be stored using environment variables.

Authentication and authorization should rely on PocketBase capabilities.

Validate all user input before processing.

------------------------------------------------
API DESIGN RULES

All APIs must follow REST principles.

Response format should be consistent:

{
  "success": true,
  "data": {},
  "error": null
}

Error responses must include meaningful messages.

------------------------------------------------
SCALABILITY CONSIDERATIONS

The system should support multiple restaurants in the future.

All relevant entities should include a restaurant_id reference.

Design the architecture so that multi-tenant support can be added later.

------------------------------------------------
LOGGING

Important system events should produce logs.

Examples:

reservation created
reservation updated
table assigned
automation triggered

Logs should help debugging and monitoring.

------------------------------------------------
SEED DATA

Provide example data for development.

Include:

1 example restaurant
10 example tables
several sample reservations
sample customers

This allows developers to test the system quickly.

------------------------------------------------
FRONTEND GUIDELINES

Use a simple modern web architecture.

Prefer component-based design.

Minimize dependencies and keep the frontend lightweight.

The floor plan visualization should be interactive and responsive.

------------------------------------------------
README REQUIREMENTS

The repository README must include:

project overview
feature list
architecture explanation
installation instructions
usage instructions
screenshots or diagrams

The README should make the project understandable to new developers.

